name: - Ancient wall paintings (Nepal series #17)-
description:
This was an ancient Buddhist temple in the village of Kyanjin Gumba (3817 m). It is not always open to the public, so I was glad that my guide Jay was able to arrange for someone to open the door for us to take a quick look inside. I was not disappointed. The old murals were stunning and very old. The light coming through the windows made it a very special experience.

5616px X 3744px
